DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any piece of work that is undertaken or attempted.:A functional unit of heredity which occupies a specific position (locus) on a particular chromosome, is capable of reproducing itself exactly at each cell division, and directs the formation of a protein or other product.:A state of connectedness between people, objects, or events; to be associated or connected with something._One of the bodies in the cell nucleus that is the bearer of genes, has the form of a delicate chromatin filament during interphase, contracts to form a compact cylinder segmented into two arms by the centromere during metaphase and anaphase stages of cell division, and is capable of reproducing its physical and chemical structure through successive cell divisions.:The point or place at which something terminates in time, space, or extent._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).

Concepts.definition: Any specifically defined piece of work that is undertaken or attempted to meet a single requirement.
A functional unit of heredity which occupies a specific position on a particular chromosome and serves as the template for a product that contributes to a phenotype or a biological function.
A state of connectedness between people, objects, or events; to be associated or connected with something.

Property.preferredDefinition: One of the bodies in the cell nucleus that is the bearer of genes, has the form of a delicate chromatin filament during interphase, contracts to form a compact cylinder segmented into two arms by the centromere during metaphase and anaphase stages of cell division, and is capable of reproducing its physical and chemical structure through successive cell divisions.:The point or place at which something terminates in time, space, or extent.

Concepts.definition: A structure found in cells that is comprised of a strand of linearized double-stranded DNA plus proteins that package the DNA in a condensed coil form and regulate chromosomal function.
The point or place at which something terminates in time, space, or extent.
